[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating library setup needs**\n\nI'm thinking about whether the jakarta.annotation-api is necessary. Without it, some features like @PostConstruct might not be covered, and that could be a problem. Spring 6 uses jakarta for EE APIs, so I’ll have to figure out if I need extra Maven dependencies for meaningful coverage. The core features might work with transitive dependencies, but I need concrete evidence to confirm if additional setup is necessary or not. I'll approach this carefully.\n\n**Inspecting EJB support in Spring 6**\n\nI'm realizing that the existing tests included org.glassfish:javax.ejb for EJB tests in version 5.3.15. However, with Spring 6, the EJB remoting classes are removed, but there are still references to jakarta.ejb in the @EJB support. I should take a closer look at the CommonAnnotationBeanPostProcessor source code to see how @EJB is implemented and how it interacts with the changes made in this latest version. There's definitely some investigation needed here!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09d13c6e0c16725c016a408215e94c8195b147416cafe761e0\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQIIcy3RnuH1B3XmjAIqlqt62VSC9ACnvOMzb6fSm3AJAaV4hnBCJkk_dBxoWzRSsxd-TekpQpKp8hDymYijuvMMiP1sI_nDqzAfoz_FlMTPA37xVDScuxL6ht4pOTDABSBZH3A_TwMmgo21bNAcSTymc-X0J3x1vDWfec1b0vaUTROxJ8tb_tdTss_jggVRW1tySL9ckb8xAbl4VOLZsPvc15Oazzj5Q7iYIlGmvvkvsewgIK1xior0UUNZEcsv6X8AISdKKduE9vWD4hRFpExwDLXJfU5Y5bl9UJIaczxsKcXhiPtUtvx9WkZOojuuCwa5kxQA3VcttTxtMoSLOh6K7R9XZpeHIhu6h9_XAOvg3xqZk2oRxYX_cNsBbCfhybOkR3eWkn2pj8pu-p6h2Q4qL-51WrhdzWOwGFncmrC1H2OqSJlb1sAqhiMeZIdDwXb9y_bGFnzayFAJHVp4M8QjEv2Nxdsmx_T8zVixtOMtfJWmO3lTAzqQKpofJ3chjaqZIL708gvf_EJRW9tnJ3ZqjgRhmk5o4R501IFFxplEfdINymwLv9rkYylxs9BOAcllZgTwGNSkWSMA1w1J-HxLkHAnh2rDe2LQBRgzLxfy7oqKsNNoYuQ3Uh8DW71AP0saX37OD9IwULog0guoj59YhWq3wfVSykS5gmz3SZHDNMZDBMjZGk3ojIoj4utZZP_a6AHrQ88PXceHewZAEvEk7vI